[normal]The extent of white working class pupils’ educational underachievement.[bold]1.1.
[normal] 
[normal]We share
[normal] the Government’s concern about the underachievement of children and young people from a white working class background and young people. We would argue that this should be a strategic priority from early years through to higher education. However,
[normal] 
[normal]it is o
[normal]ur view that  this is a difficult question to answer empirically as the group und
[normal]er discussion do not exist as a 
[normal]clearly identifiable statistical cohort.
