[normal]An analysis of three years of data for Buckinghamshire by FSM for white British boys and girls, compared to all boys and girls with and without FSM shows is that:
[normal]•
[normal]              
[normal]For non-FSM pupils, at bo
[normal]th Key Stages 2 and 4, White British are above or at the average for all FSM pupils
[normal]•
[normal]              
[normal]For FSM pupils, the same is broadly true at KS2, although there was a dip for WB pupils in English in 2011
[normal]•
[normal]              
[normal]For FSM pupils at KS4, generally the White British pupils are
[normal] below the overall average for FSM.
[normal]•
[normal]              
[normal]There is a very big gender gap for FSM pupils both in English at KS2 and overall at KS4. This applies overall and to White British pupils, with girls outperforming boys.
