[normal]What role Government can play in [bold]delivering improved educational outcomes for white working class pupils. [bold]&#xa0;[bold]6.1.
[normal]i)
[normal] 
[normal]Develop 
[normal]a nationally adopted statistical definition 
[normal]of white working class learners 
[normal]which enables analysis of
[normal] 
[normal]achievement
[normal] and progress, the identification of areas where underachievement is most pronounced
[normal] and the 
[normal]analysis of the 
[normal]impact of interventions
[normal] 
[normal]6.1.
[normal]ii) Raise the profile of pastoral support to address emotional or behavioural barriers to learning to support the impa
[normal]ct of high quality teaching and learning
[normal]6.1. 
[normal]iii) C
[normal]ontinue to support the collation and dissemination of evidence based good practice as has happened with  the Sutton Trust materials to support the use of the pupil premium.
[normal]6.1. 
[normal]iv) R
[normal]ecognise and celebrat
[normal]e a wider range of successful outcomes of education raising the status of work and work based training at the same time as ensuring those who choose this route has a high quality educational support to ensure they can adapt to changing labour trends and te
[normal]chnological developments
[normal]6.1. v) Share and facilitate the development of best practice in building strong links between schools and communities they serve, including the development of parental hubs in schools, education programmes for parents and an incre
[normal]ased focus of the role of parents as key partners in early years education.
